#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.244"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.244:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.244:0.2"
msgid "19. Āsīvisavagga"
msgstr "19. The Simile of the Vipers"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.244:0.3"
msgid "244. Dukkhadhammasutta"
msgstr "244. Entailing Suffering"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.244:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbesaṃyeva dukkhadhammānaṃ samudayañca "
"atthaṅgamañca yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when a mendicant truly understands the origin and ending of all "
"things that entail suffering,"

msgctxt "sn35.244:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tathā kho panassa kāmā diṭṭhā honti, yathāssa kāme passato, yo kāmesu "
"kāmacchando kāmasneho kāmamucchā kāmapariḷāho, so nānuseti."
msgstr ""
"then they’ve seen sensual pleasures in such a way that they have no "
"underlying tendency for desire, affection, stupefaction, and passion for "
"sensual pleasures."

# See BB’s note on readings. MS uses nānussavanti below.
msgctxt "sn35.244:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tathā kho panassa cāro ca vihāro ca anubuddho hoti, yathā carantaṃ "
"viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā nānusenti."
msgstr ""
"And they’ve awakened to a way of conduct and a way of living such that, when "
"they live in that way, bad, unskillful qualities of desire and grief don’t "
"overwhelm them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.244:2.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, sabbesaṃyeva dukkhadhammānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca "
"yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant truly understand the origin and ending of all "
"things that entail suffering?"

msgctxt "sn35.244:2.2"
msgid "‘Iti rūpaṃ, iti rūpassa samudayo, iti rūpassa atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr "‘Such is form, such is the origin of form, such is the ending of form."

msgctxt "sn35.244:2.3"
msgid "iti vedanā …"
msgstr "Such is feeling …"

msgctxt "sn35.244:2.4"
msgid "iti saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn35.244:2.5"
msgid "iti saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn35.244:2.6"
msgid "iti viññāṇaṃ, iti viññāṇassa samudayo, iti viññāṇassa atthaṅgamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"consciousness, such is the origin of consciousness, such is the ending of "
"consciousness.’"

msgctxt "sn35.244:2.7"
msgid ""
"evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbesaṃyeva dukkhadhammānaṃ samudayañca "
"atthaṅgamañca yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant truly understands the origin and ending of all things "
"that entail suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.189"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.244:3.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno kāmā diṭṭhā honti? Yathāssa kāme passato, yo "
"kāmesu kāmacchando kāmasneho kāmamucchā kāmapariḷāho, so nānuseti."
msgstr ""
"And how has a mendicant seen sensual pleasures in such a way that they have "
"no underlying tendency for desire, affection, stupefaction, and passion for "
"sensual pleasures?"

msgctxt "sn35.244:3.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, aṅgārakāsu sādhikaporisā puṇṇā aṅgārānaṃ vītaccikānaṃ "
"vītadhūmānaṃ. Atha puriso āgaccheyya jīvitukāmo amaritukāmo sukhakāmo "
"dukkhapaṭikūlo. Tamenaṃ dve balavanto purisā nānābāhāsu gahetvā, taṃ "
"aṅgārakāsuṃ upakaḍḍheyyuṃ. So iticīticeva kāyaṃ sannāmeyya."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a pit of glowing coals deeper than a man’s height, filled "
"with glowing coals that neither flamed nor smoked. Then a person would come "
"along who wants to live and doesn’t want to die, who wants to be happy and "
"recoils from pain. Then two strong men grab would grab each arm and drag "
"them towards the pit of glowing coals. They’d writhe and struggle to and fro."

msgctxt "sn35.244:3.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

#. VAR: Ñātañhi → aññāṇañhi (s1-3) | ñāṇaṃ (mr)
#. VAR: purisassa → purisassa hoti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1) | purisassa hetu hoti (mr)
msgctxt "sn35.244:3.4"
msgid ""
"Ñātañhi, bhikkhave, tassa purisassa imañcāhaṃ aṅgārakāsuṃ papatissāmi, "
"tatonidānaṃ maraṇaṃ vā nigacchissāmi maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhanti."
msgstr ""
"For that man knows: ‘If I fall in that pit of glowing coals, that’d result "
"in my death or deadly pain.’"

msgctxt "sn35.244:3.5"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā diṭṭhā honti, yathāssa "
"kāme passato, yo kāmesu kāmacchando kāmasneho kāmamucchā kāmapariḷāho, so "
"nānuseti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when a mendicant has seen sensual pleasures as like a pit "
"of glowing coals, they have no underlying tendency for desire, affection, "
"stupefaction, and passion for sensual pleasures."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: nānussavanti → nānusavanti (pts1) | nānusenti (mr)
msgctxt "sn35.244:4.1"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno cāro ca vihāro ca anubuddho hoti, yathā "
"carantaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā nānussavanti?"
msgstr ""
"And how has a mendicant awakened to a way of conduct and a way of living "
"such that, when they live in that way, bad, unskillful qualities of desire "
"and grief don’t overwhelm them?"

msgctxt "sn35.244:4.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso bahukaṇṭakaṃ dāyaṃ paviseyya. Tassa puratopi "
"kaṇṭako, pacchatopi kaṇṭako, uttaratopi kaṇṭako, dakkhiṇatopi kaṇṭako, "
"heṭṭhatopi kaṇṭako, uparitopi kaṇṭako. So satova abhikkameyya, satova "
"paṭikkameyya: ‘mā maṃ kaṇṭako’ti."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a person was to enter a thicket full of thorns. They’d have thorns "
"in front and behind, to the left and right, below and above. So they’d go "
"forward mindfully and come back mindfully, thinking: ‘May I not get any "
"thorns!’"

# Quote mark here is incorrect in MS.
msgctxt "sn35.244:4.3"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, yaṃ loke piyarūpaṃ sātarūpaṃ, ayaṃ vuccati ariyassa "
"vinaye kaṇṭako”ti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, whatever in the world seems nice and pleasant is called a "
"thorn in the training of the noble one."

#. VAR: viditvā → kaṇḍako. taṃ kaṇḍakoti iti viditvā (bj)
#. VAR: saṃvaro ca asaṃvaro ca → asaṃvaro ca saṃvaro ca (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn35.244:4.4"
msgid "Iti viditvā saṃvaro ca asaṃvaro ca veditabbo."
msgstr ""
"When they understand what a thorn is, they should understand restraint and "
"lack of restraint."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.244:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, asaṃvaro hoti?"
msgstr "And how is someone unrestrained?"

msgctxt "sn35.244:5.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā piyarūpe rūpe adhimuccati, "
"appiyarūpe rūpe byāpajjati, anupaṭṭhitakāyassati ca viharati parittacetaso, "
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who sees a sight with the eye. If it’s pleasant they hold "
"on to it, but if it’s unpleasant they dislike it. They live with mindfulness "
"of the body unestablished and their heart restricted. "

msgctxt "sn35.244:5.3"
msgid ""
"tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, yatthassa te "
"uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom "
"where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left "
"over."

msgctxt "sn35.244:5.4"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …"
msgstr "They hear a sound … smell an odor … taste a flavor … feel a touch …"

msgctxt "sn35.244:5.5"
msgid ""
"manasā dhammaṃ viññāya piyarūpe dhamme adhimuccati, appiyarūpe dhamme "
"byāpajjati, anupaṭṭhitakāyassati ca viharati parittacetaso, "
msgstr ""
"know a thought with the mind. If it’s pleasant they hold on to it, but if it’"
"s unpleasant they dislike it. They live with mindfulness of the body "
"unestablished and a limited heart. "

msgctxt "sn35.244:5.6"
msgid ""
"tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te "
"uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom "
"where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left "
"over."

msgctxt "sn35.244:5.7"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, asaṃvaro hoti."
msgstr "This is how someone is unrestrained."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.190"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.244:6.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, saṃvaro hoti?"
msgstr "And how is someone restrained?"

msgctxt "sn35.244:6.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā piyarūpe rūpe nādhimuccati, "
"appiyarūpe rūpe na byāpajjati, upaṭṭhitakāyassati ca viharati "
"appamāṇacetaso, "
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who sees a sight with the eye. If it’s pleasant they don’t "
"hold on to it, and if it’s unpleasant they don’t dislike it. They live with "
"mindfulness of the body established and a limitless heart. "

msgctxt "sn35.244:6.3"
msgid ""
"tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, yatthassa te uppannā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"And they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where "
"those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over."

msgctxt "sn35.244:6.4"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …"
msgstr "They hear a sound … smell an odor … taste a flavor … feel a touch …"

msgctxt "sn35.244:6.5"
msgid ""
"manasā dhammaṃ viññāya piyarūpe dhamme nādhimuccati, appiyarūpe dhamme na "
"byāpajjati, upaṭṭhitakāyassati ca viharati appamāṇacetaso, "
msgstr ""
"know a thought with the mind. If it’s pleasant they don’t hold on to it, and "
"if it’s unpleasant they don’t dislike it. They live with mindfulness of the "
"body established and a limitless heart. "

msgctxt "sn35.244:6.6"
msgid ""
"tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, yatthassa te uppannā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"And they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where "
"those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over."

msgctxt "sn35.244:6.7"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, saṃvaro hoti."
msgstr "This is how someone is restrained."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.244:7.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno evaṃ carato evaṃ viharato kadāci karahaci "
"satisammosā uppajjanti, pāpakā akusalā sarasaṅkappā saṃyojaniyā, dandho, "
"bhikkhave, satuppādo. Atha kho naṃ khippameva pajahati vinodeti byantīkaroti "
"anabhāvaṃ gameti."
msgstr ""
"Though that mendicant conducts themselves and lives in this way, every so "
"often they might lose mindfulness, and bad, unskillful memories and thoughts "
"prone to fetters arise. If this happens, their mindfulness is slow to come "
"up, but they quickly give them up, get rid of, eliminate, and exterminate "
"those thoughts."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
#. VAR: divasaṃsantatte → divasasantatte (bj)
msgctxt "sn35.244:8.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso divasaṃsantatte ayokaṭāhe dve vā tīṇi vā "
"udakaphusitāni nipāteyya. Dandho, bhikkhave, udakaphusitānaṃ nipāto, atha "
"kho naṃ khippameva parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ gaccheyya."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was an iron cauldron that had been heated all day, and a "
"person let two or three drops of water fall onto it. The drops would be slow "
"to fall, but they’d quickly dry up and evaporate."

msgctxt "sn35.244:8.2"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, tassa ce bhikkhuno evaṃ carato, evaṃ viharato kadāci "
"karahaci satisammosā uppajjanti pāpakā akusalā sarasaṅkappā saṃyojaniyā, "
"dandho, bhikkhave, satuppādo. Atha kho naṃ khippameva pajahati vinodeti "
"byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, though that mendicant conducts themselves and lives in this "
"way, every so often they might lose mindfulness, and bad, unskillful "
"memories and thoughts prone to fetters arise. If this happens, their "
"mindfulness is slow to come up, but they quickly give them up, get rid of, "
"eliminate, and exterminate those thoughts."

msgctxt "sn35.244:8.3"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno cāro ca vihāro ca anubuddho hoti; yathā "
"carantaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā nānussavanti."
msgstr ""
"This is how a mendicant has awakened to a way of conduct and a way of living "
"such that, when they live in that way, bad, unskillful qualities of desire "
"and grief don’t overwhelm them."

msgctxt "sn35.244:8.4"
msgid ""
"Tañce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ evaṃ carantaṃ evaṃ viharantaṃ rājāno vā "
"rājamahāmattā vā mittā vā amaccā vā ñātī vā sālohitā vā, bhogehi abhihaṭṭhuṃ "
"pavāreyyuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"While that mendicant conducts themselves in this way and lives in this way, "
"if rulers or their ministers, friends or colleagues, relatives or family "
"should invite them to accept wealth, saying:"

#. VAR: ehi → ehambho (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "sn35.244:8.5"
msgid ""
"‘ehi, bho purisa, kiṃ te ime kāsāvā anudahanti, kiṃ muṇḍo kapālamanucarasi, "
"ehi hīnāyāvattitvā bhoge ca bhuñjassu, puññāni ca karohī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Please, mister, why let these ocher robes torment you? Why follow the "
"practice of shaving your head and carrying an alms bowl? Come, return to a "
"lesser life, enjoy wealth, and make merit!’"

msgctxt "sn35.244:8.6"
msgid ""
"So vata, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ caranto evaṃ viharanto sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya "
"hīnāyāvattissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"It’s simply impossible for a mendicant who conducts themselves in this way "
"and lives in this way to reject the training and return to a lesser life."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.191"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.244:9.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, gaṅgā nadī pācīnaninnā pācīnapoṇā pācīnapabbhārā. "
"Atha mahājanakāyo āgaccheyya kuddālapiṭakaṃ ādāya: ‘mayaṃ imaṃ gaṅgaṃ nadiṃ "
"pacchāninnaṃ karissāma pacchāpoṇaṃ pacchāpabbhāran’ti."
msgstr ""
"Suppose that, although the Ganges river slants, slopes, and inclines to the "
"east, a large crowd were to come along with a spade and basket, saying: ‘We’"
"ll make this Ganges river slant, slope, and incline to the west!’"

msgctxt "sn35.244:9.2"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn35.244:9.3"
msgid ""
"api nu kho so mahājanakāyo gaṅgaṃ nadiṃ pacchāninnaṃ kareyya pacchāpoṇaṃ "
"pacchāpabbhāran”ti?"
msgstr "Would they still succeed?”"

msgctxt "sn35.244:9.4"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir."

msgctxt "sn35.244:9.5"
msgid "“Taṃ kissa hetu”?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn35.244:9.6"
msgid "“Gaṅgā, bhante, nadī pācīnaninnā pācīnapoṇā pācīnapabbhārā;"
msgstr "The Ganges river slants, slopes, and inclines to the east."

msgctxt "sn35.244:9.7"
msgid "sā na sukarā pacchāninnā kātuṃ pacchāpoṇā pacchāpabbhārā."
msgstr "It’s not easy to make it slant, slope, and incline to the west."

msgctxt "sn35.244:9.8"
msgid "Yāvadeva ca pana so mahājanakāyo kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti."
msgstr "That large crowd will eventually get weary and frustrated.”"

msgctxt "sn35.244:9.9"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, tañce bhikkhuṃ evaṃ carantaṃ evaṃ viharantaṃ rājāno "
"vā rājamahāmattā vā mittā vā amaccā vā ñātī vā sālohitā vā bhogehi "
"abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreyyuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, while that mendicant conducts themselves in this way and "
"lives in this way, if rulers or their ministers, friends or colleagues, "
"relatives or family should invite them to accept wealth, saying:"

msgctxt "sn35.244:9.10"
msgid ""
"‘ehi, bho purisa, kiṃ te ime kāsāvā anudahanti, kiṃ muṇḍo kapālamanucarasi, "
"ehi hīnāyāvattitvā bhoge ca bhuñjassu, puññāni ca karohī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Please, mister, why let these ocher robes torment you? Why follow the "
"practice of shaving your head and carrying an alms bowl? Come, return to a "
"lesser life, enjoy wealth, and make merit!’"

msgctxt "sn35.244:9.11"
msgid ""
"So vata, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ caranto evaṃ viharanto sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya "
"hīnāyāvattissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"It’s simply impossible for a mendicant who conducts themselves in this way "
"and lives in this way to reject the training and return to a lesser life."

msgctxt "sn35.244:9.12"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

# BB mistakenly inserts “give up the training” here and in the parallel passage at SN 52.8. At SN 45.160, he correctly omits it.
#. VAR: tathā → tatha (bj) | tañca (s1-3, km) | kañca (mr)
msgctxt "sn35.244:9.13"
msgid ""
"Yañhi taṃ, bhikkhave, cittaṃ dīgharattaṃ vivekaninnaṃ vivekapoṇaṃ "
"vivekapabbhāraṃ, tathā hīnāyāvattissatīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Because for a long time that mendicant’s mind has slanted, sloped, and "
"inclined to seclusion. So it’s impossible for them to return to a lesser "
"life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.244:9.14"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
